WEBVTT

00:06.798 --> 00:10.218
Are athletes born athletes?

00:11.219 --> 00:13.763
What about astronauts or pop stars?

00:15.306 --> 00:17.308
No one knows at birth.

00:18.560 --> 00:21.563
But then, what about witches?

01:23.083 --> 01:24.542
Sorry for getting it dirty.

01:25.043 --> 01:26.669
I'm almost done washing.

01:30.340 --> 01:32.258
It'll turn right back to normal.

01:32.342 --> 01:35.428
This spring is under a spell!

01:59.661 --> 02:01.913
It never gets old. It's so beautiful.

02:01.996 --> 02:04.582
Magic is amazing!

02:08.169 --> 02:10.588
The world is brimming with magic.

02:11.131 --> 02:13.967
It's a practical miracle
we can't live without.

02:16.094 --> 02:18.429
But we don't know how it works.

02:18.513 --> 02:19.848
THE MAGIC OF BEGINNINGS

02:19.931 --> 02:23.351
Only witches can cast spells.

02:25.061 --> 02:29.190
Ordinary people can only receive magic.

02:30.400 --> 02:32.485
We can never become witches.

02:35.613 --> 02:38.867
Those born witches are so lucky.

02:46.583 --> 02:51.796
Oh, sheet, my sheet...
turn into a flying cloak!

02:56.092 --> 02:57.177
Oh no!

02:57.260 --> 03:00.305
Wait! No!
That's not what I meant by flying!

03:17.071 --> 03:18.198
It's a pegasus carriage!

03:31.836 --> 03:34.505
It's my first time seeing one land!

03:37.050 --> 03:40.386
Mom! There's a pegasus carriage outside!

03:41.429 --> 03:42.764
Mom!

03:44.265 --> 03:46.351
Mom!

03:53.608 --> 03:55.777
I'm sorry! I didn't see you.

03:56.361 --> 03:59.739
It's okay. My fault for standing
in front of the door.

03:59.822 --> 04:01.699
Oh, I can't believe this!

04:01.783 --> 04:04.702
Look at this!
I can't believe they have this here.

04:04.786 --> 04:08.122
Oh, but don't you think
the oxalis embroidery is outdated?

04:08.206 --> 04:11.417
More importantly, look!
This is Harian-knit lace!

04:11.501 --> 04:12.585
That's amazing!

04:12.669 --> 04:15.338
It sold out instantly in the castle town.

04:16.506 --> 04:19.759
Those customers must have come
on a pegasus carriage!

04:21.511 --> 04:23.054
Oh, no, not me.

04:23.638 --> 04:26.724
Excuse me, ma'am,
do you have more lace like this?

04:26.808 --> 04:28.768
Yes, right away!

04:29.560 --> 04:31.896
Coco, help me out if you're here.

04:33.273 --> 04:35.024
What would you like, sir?

04:35.108 --> 04:38.778
I'd like some smoke-colored fabric,
but if you're busy, I can wait.

04:38.861 --> 04:40.780
I can measure it out for you.

04:40.863 --> 04:41.781
You can?

04:41.864 --> 04:43.741
Coco is quite good.

04:43.825 --> 04:44.659
Is that so?

04:47.829 --> 04:50.873
Hey, can I go see
the pegasus carriage when I'm done?

04:50.957 --> 04:52.208
What?

04:52.292 --> 04:53.626
A pegasus carriage is here!

04:54.335 --> 04:55.461
A pegasus carriage?

04:55.545 --> 04:58.506
You're not going to play with
customer property, are you?

04:58.589 --> 05:00.341
Don't worry. I'll just look!

05:02.802 --> 05:06.347
I'll stop saying I want to be a witch.

05:10.601 --> 05:12.520
Only if you finish your work early.

05:13.062 --> 05:14.480
Yes!

05:15.606 --> 05:18.151
Thank you for waiting!
How much would you like?

05:18.234 --> 05:19.360
Oh, here.

05:19.444 --> 05:20.570
I'll take care of it.

06:00.943 --> 06:01.861
Wow.

06:03.529 --> 06:05.323
That's quite the focus.

06:05.406 --> 06:06.741
Steady hands too.

06:06.824 --> 06:09.869
Clean lines and decisive cuts.

06:09.952 --> 06:12.789
And most of all,
your finish is so careful and exact.

06:13.539 --> 06:16.542
I had no idea
this village had such a wonderful artisan.

06:18.211 --> 06:19.504
This is magic.

06:20.963 --> 06:25.385
No! My work is nothing like that!

06:25.468 --> 06:28.388
Magic is something more mysterious,
more sparkly,

06:28.471 --> 06:30.390
more precious, and beautiful.

06:30.473 --> 06:32.100
And it's more...

06:32.850 --> 06:33.684
it's more...

06:34.185 --> 06:37.522
it's more... sacred.

06:38.189 --> 06:40.400
What am I even saying?

06:40.900 --> 06:43.069
You really love magic, don't you?

06:45.696 --> 06:47.573
May I ask you why?

06:53.454 --> 06:57.583
When I was little,
I was taken to a festival at the castle.

06:58.126 --> 07:00.837
I met a witch wearing a mask there.

07:19.021 --> 07:20.481
You there.

07:22.191 --> 07:24.819
Would you like to buy a picture book
about magic?

07:27.447 --> 07:32.493
Magic? I like picture books,
but what's magic?

07:33.077 --> 07:37.081
Magic is a miracle
that brings color to the world.

07:38.749 --> 07:41.169
The pegasus carriages
that soar across the sky,

07:41.252 --> 07:44.130
and the eternal springs
that keep their water pure.

07:44.213 --> 07:49.677
And even the cobblestones that glow
when you step on them.

07:49.760 --> 07:51.762
All of it is magic.

07:54.056 --> 07:55.641
This is so pretty!

07:55.725 --> 07:59.604
Magic is so amazing! I love magic!

08:00.104 --> 08:02.398
Now with a free wand included!

08:05.985 --> 08:08.654
So you were tricked into buying that?

08:09.238 --> 08:11.699
You said you wanted to eat
grilled strawberries.

08:11.782 --> 08:16.287
Well, I was chasing a butterfly,
and then I met a person with a pointy hat.

08:16.370 --> 08:18.331
You already told me that.

08:18.414 --> 08:22.668
So it's a picture book about magic!
And a free wand!

08:25.171 --> 08:28.549
Okay, Coco, it's time to go home.
It's getting late.

08:28.633 --> 08:29.592
Mom!

08:30.259 --> 08:35.932
When I grow up, I'm going to be a witch
who brings color to the world!

08:36.015 --> 08:37.266
That's impossible.

08:37.350 --> 08:38.601
Why is that?!

08:41.062 --> 08:46.359
You can't become a witch unless
you were born with the power of magic.

08:46.901 --> 08:50.780
Ordinary people don't have
the innate ability to become witches.

08:52.657 --> 08:54.492
Now, Coco. Let's go home.

08:54.575 --> 08:55.701
But look!

08:55.785 --> 08:58.704
The path glows when I step on it.

09:01.666 --> 09:06.170
Then, if it keeps glowing
all the way home,

09:06.921 --> 09:09.090
maybe you can use magic too.

09:18.683 --> 09:23.396
Since then, I just like looking at it.
Or maybe I just can't let it go.

09:23.980 --> 09:26.190
Can you tell me more about what--

09:27.984 --> 09:29.318
What was that?

09:30.987 --> 09:33.364
Hey, stop it. Stay still.

09:34.407 --> 09:35.533
Easy, easy.

09:45.376 --> 09:47.503
What are you doing? Jeez.

09:47.587 --> 09:49.505
Shut up. Ow...

09:49.589 --> 09:50.631
Are you okay?

09:51.549 --> 09:52.717
What happened?

09:53.217 --> 09:55.177
I didn't do anything. It just broke.

09:55.261 --> 09:58.389
Huh? That's not true.
Tanerl went under it!

09:58.472 --> 09:59.849
Tattle-tale!

09:59.932 --> 10:02.393
He hit his head on the bottom,
and it flipped over.

10:02.476 --> 10:04.437
Oh my! What in the world?

10:05.229 --> 10:06.981
Our pegasus carriage...

10:07.064 --> 10:09.233
We borrowed it from Father too.

10:09.317 --> 10:12.987
Please accept my apologies.
The village children behaved terribly.

10:13.070 --> 10:15.281
An apology won't help.

10:15.364 --> 10:17.366
We can't go home without the carriage!

10:17.450 --> 10:19.243
I don't know what more to say.

10:20.536 --> 10:21.412
Pardon me.

10:23.789 --> 10:25.166
Would you like me to fix it?

10:27.043 --> 10:29.920
It doesn't look like
the damage is that bad.

10:30.004 --> 10:32.173
Excuse me, but who are you?

10:32.256 --> 10:35.885
My apologies. I forgot my signature item.

10:42.016 --> 10:45.436
Qifrey the witch, at your service.

10:48.397 --> 10:50.191
- A pointed hat.
- A pointed hat.

10:50.858 --> 10:51.942
You can fix it?

10:52.026 --> 10:52.860
Yes.

10:53.402 --> 10:55.863
Thank you, Mr. Witch.

10:55.946 --> 10:56.906
It'll be all right.

10:57.657 --> 11:00.451
I just have to recast the spell
on the bottom of the carriage.

11:00.534 --> 11:02.328
I'd love for you to do it.

11:02.828 --> 11:04.288
Please leave it to me.

11:04.372 --> 11:06.582
But I can't really do it outside.

11:06.666 --> 11:08.751
You can use our workshop!

11:10.127 --> 11:11.545
It's okay, right, Mom?

11:13.214 --> 11:14.048
I mean,

11:14.882 --> 11:17.051
he's a real witch.

11:18.260 --> 11:20.888
I might even get to see it.

11:21.889 --> 11:24.725
The moment he casts a spell.

11:33.693 --> 11:35.444
While I'm casting the spell,

11:35.528 --> 11:39.073
I'd like you to keep watch outside
so no one peeks inside.

11:39.699 --> 11:43.160
Don't let anyone in, no matter what.
Got it?

11:46.288 --> 11:48.708
Life isn't that easy, I guess.

11:50.000 --> 11:52.712
But I wonder why I can't watch.

11:53.754 --> 11:57.091
There is so much magic in the world,

11:57.174 --> 11:59.969
but we don't know how to cast it.

12:00.553 --> 12:02.596
Only witches know...

12:03.431 --> 12:04.682
the secret.

12:11.188 --> 12:12.189
Huh?

12:12.690 --> 12:13.858
Whoa, it's slippery.

12:15.818 --> 12:17.570
Hey! What are you doing?

12:17.653 --> 12:18.571
Busted!

12:18.654 --> 12:20.239
It's just her. It’ll be fine.

12:20.322 --> 12:22.366
Can we peek in from here?

12:23.325 --> 12:24.326
Wait!

12:24.410 --> 12:25.995
Keep your voice down!

12:26.078 --> 12:27.079
Out of the way!

12:40.050 --> 12:41.969
Seriously? Lame.

12:42.052 --> 12:43.429
For real.

12:51.562 --> 12:52.396
What?

13:23.636 --> 13:25.387
No, I can't.

13:25.471 --> 13:28.057
But I really want to see. But I shouldn't.

13:55.918 --> 13:57.211
He's drawing...

14:01.423 --> 14:04.176
magic... with a pen?!

14:06.345 --> 14:07.721
Then that means...

14:08.931 --> 14:10.266
it isn't a wand!

14:12.101 --> 14:12.977
Magic is

14:14.603 --> 14:16.021
not something you cast.

14:17.982 --> 14:19.233
It's something you draw!

14:20.776 --> 14:21.986
Now, then.

14:22.778 --> 14:24.029
I'm done.

14:33.038 --> 14:34.623
Good job.

14:53.225 --> 14:55.561
I'm a bit relieved.

14:56.562 --> 14:59.064
With you loving magic so much,

14:59.607 --> 15:05.195
I thought that maybe you would say
you wanted to go with the witch.

15:07.239 --> 15:09.491
I already lost your father to illness.

15:10.034 --> 15:13.996
If you left too, I'd...

15:14.079 --> 15:17.875
I'd never say that!
I couldn't leave you all by yourself.

15:21.337 --> 15:25.174
Thank you. You're such a sweet girl, Coco.

15:43.442 --> 15:44.526
Good night.

15:44.610 --> 15:46.070
Good night.

15:50.824 --> 15:53.160
It's nothing. Good night.

15:54.078 --> 15:55.079
Good night.

16:03.754 --> 16:06.924
...you would say
you wanted to go with the witch.

16:24.692 --> 16:27.403
All the patterns
drawn in the picture book...

16:28.112 --> 16:31.240
The magic wand wasn't just a freebie.

16:32.366 --> 16:35.285
The pen itself was the magic wand!

16:49.049 --> 16:52.636
I'm sorry, Mom. I won't go anywhere.

16:53.178 --> 16:54.430
But let me try.

17:44.229 --> 17:45.064
Huh?

17:47.733 --> 17:50.194
Oh, it didn't work.

17:50.277 --> 17:53.405
Figures. I knew it couldn't be that easy.

18:19.973 --> 18:22.559
It glowed! I just used magic!

18:22.643 --> 18:26.897
Amazing! It's magic! It's magic!
It's real magic! What should I do?!

18:28.107 --> 18:29.733
So it is drawn.

18:29.817 --> 18:32.277
But I wasn't supposed to look.
Will I get in trouble?

18:37.699 --> 18:40.744
But just one more time.
Just one more page.

18:54.550 --> 18:57.219
A picture book. A picture book, huh?

18:59.054 --> 19:01.223
I can't get it out of my mind.

19:04.143 --> 19:05.060
Surely not?!

19:08.147 --> 19:11.150
That one was a fire spell!
No, no! Don't burn!

19:13.443 --> 19:14.486
That was close!

19:15.904 --> 19:16.738
But...

19:18.740 --> 19:20.742
I feel like I'm getting the hang of this.

19:21.368 --> 19:24.496
The bigger ones are stronger
than the smaller ones,

19:24.580 --> 19:27.833
and the ones I drew neatly
last longer than the messy ones!

19:28.834 --> 19:31.712
It's hard to draw them big and neatly.

19:32.254 --> 19:34.131
Qifrey drew them so easily.

19:34.882 --> 19:35.757
Oh, that's it!

19:41.346 --> 19:42.764
Just as I thought.

19:42.848 --> 19:46.518
If I trace over the pattern,
I can draw them neatly!

19:56.153 --> 19:57.154
I did it!

20:18.175 --> 20:19.051
You drew something.

20:19.134 --> 20:22.179
What did you draw?
What magic did you draw?!

20:22.262 --> 20:25.766
I don't know! I just traced the pattern
from the picture book!

20:29.770 --> 20:30.604
Mom!

20:36.693 --> 20:37.527
Run!

20:43.867 --> 20:45.786
No. That can't be...

20:46.662 --> 20:48.789
Mom! Mom!

20:48.872 --> 20:50.165
Mom!

20:50.249 --> 20:52.042
This is forbidden magic--

20:52.125 --> 20:53.293
No! Let me go!

20:53.377 --> 20:55.420
You'll get caught up in it too--

20:55.504 --> 20:56.797
I have to save my mom!

20:56.880 --> 20:59.883
It's no use! This is magic! And it's bad--

20:59.967 --> 21:00.801
Oh no!

21:06.974 --> 21:08.642
Mom!

21:10.227 --> 21:11.979
No!

21:16.942 --> 21:17.859
I'm sorry!

21:18.819 --> 21:20.153
I didn't know.

21:20.862 --> 21:22.656
Of course you didn't.

21:23.282 --> 21:25.659
It's kept secret
to prevent things like this.

21:26.702 --> 21:30.122
Special ink, prescribed seals.

21:30.205 --> 21:33.041
With those, anyone can use magic.

21:33.125 --> 21:35.669
It's the absolute secret of witches.

21:36.628 --> 21:40.173
And now that you know,
I have to erase your memories.

21:44.177 --> 21:49.057
No! If my memories are erased,
then who will save Mom?!

21:49.933 --> 21:51.560
I'm sorry, but...

21:52.269 --> 21:54.354
I don't remember the magic I drew,

21:54.438 --> 21:56.773
but I can recite the contents
of the picture book by heart!

21:57.274 --> 21:59.776
If I forget that, then my mom...

22:01.111 --> 22:02.070
The picture book...

22:02.738 --> 22:04.114
Of course!

22:04.197 --> 22:08.118
If that book belongs to them,
I won't be able to track them.

22:08.785 --> 22:12.122
If I erase her memories,
then the trail will go cold.

22:12.998 --> 22:15.292
So you remember what the book was like?

22:15.375 --> 22:16.209
Yes.

22:16.710 --> 22:18.754
And what page the seal was drawn on?

22:18.837 --> 22:19.838
Yes... Yes.

22:22.215 --> 22:25.344
If I find the same book,
then the seal will be in it.

22:28.055 --> 22:30.015
If you know which seal it is,

22:30.098 --> 22:31.892
would you be able to save my mother?

22:34.936 --> 22:37.981
I might... be able to.

22:38.648 --> 22:39.733
Mr. Qifrey!

22:40.942 --> 22:43.070
Please, don't erase my memories!

22:43.153 --> 22:46.323
I'll do anything
if it means I can save my mother!

22:48.533 --> 22:49.910
Can you keep the secret?

22:50.410 --> 22:51.536
I promise!

22:53.038 --> 22:54.790
Do you have the will to learn?

22:54.873 --> 22:55.874
Learn...

22:57.417 --> 22:59.878
If you are to retain the truth
you've learned,

23:00.379 --> 23:03.382
then you'll have to stand alongside
us who keep the secret.

23:04.508 --> 23:07.761
This is the only option
to keep your memories intact!

23:10.514 --> 23:11.640
From now on...

23:13.642 --> 23:15.560
you will become a witch.

23:33.620 --> 23:35.914
Subtitle translation by: Emily Noguchi

23:36.498 --> 23:40.919
EPISODE 2
THE SCHOOL IN THE MEADOW
